Your Honor,

I stand before this honorable court today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I fully accept responsibility for my actions and understand the seriousness of the offense I have committed.

In the events leading up to the incident, I failed to consider the court's previous order and disregarded the fact that I was disqualified from driving. I allowed my lapse in judgment to cloud my decision-making, resulting in me getting into a car and driving to a supermarket. I deeply regret my thoughtlessness and the disregard I showed for the court's instruction.

I want to express my sincere remorse for my actions. Although I am embarrassed by my behavior, I am thankful for this opportunity to address the court and take accountability for my wrongdoing. I understand that pleading guilty is a significant mitigating factor, as it demonstrates my willingness to accept the consequences of my actions.

I would like to assure the court and the prosecution that I am committed to making amends for my behavior. I am open to any actions or measures that can help me improve and prevent similar offenses from occurring in the future. If there are driving courses or programs available that would educate me on the importance of adhering to driving regulations and the potential consequences of violating them, I humbly request the court's guidance and would eagerly participate.

Furthermore, I want to emphasize that I have no prior criminal record. While I acknowledge that my recent disqualification from driving is indicative of a lapse in judgment, I hope that the court considers my clean past record as an additional mitigating factor.

Your Honor, I also want to bring to the court's attention that I have experienced significant personal consequences as a result of my actions. Not only do I feel deep regret and embarrassment, but I have also suffered financially due to the loss of my driving privileges. These hardships have served as a powerful lesson and have acted as a strong deterrent against any future lapses in judgment.

I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding in this matter. I assure you that I have taken this incident seriously and have reflected upon the potential consequences of my actions. As a contributing member of society, I am committed to learning from this mistake and becoming a better individual going forward.

Thank you, Your Honor, for allowing me the opportunity to address the court today and plead guilty to the offense I have committed.

